# Software Factory Checklist Enforcement

## Full Template Required

Never use an abbreviated 5-line summary checklist. Always use:

`.cursor/skills/software-factory/execution/scripts/checklist-template.md`

## Completion States

Every checklist item must end in one of two states:

- `[x]` — checked complete with evidence
- `[SKIP]` — with explicit skip reason

Unchecked items are **execution failures**, not TODOs.

## Validator Gate

Before MCP `completed` status move:

```bash
python .cursor/skills/rareangels-light-overnight/scripts/validate_sf_checklist.py --wo <n>
```

Must exit 0.

## SF State Reflection

Reflect state to SF at every phase boundary via `edit_work_order` + `add_comment`. See `.cursor/skills/rareangels-coding-process/references/sf-state-reflection.md`.

The `completed` move is gated by posting the evidence comment FIRST, then moving status.

## Safe Commit + Push

After every WO: stage only owned paths → commit → `git push origin main`. Never `--force` / `--force-with-lease` / `--no-verify`.
